During a press briefing aboard Air Force One en route to Cedar Rapids, Iowa, Lindsay Walters, Deputy Press Secretary, discussed President Trump's upcoming visit to highlight precision agriculture and discuss trade. The President, along with Secretary Perdue, Secretary Ross, and Ambassador Branstad, will be meeting with individuals who are using cutting-edge technology in the agricultural sector. The President will emphasize the importance of advancing agriculture and increasing broadband connectivity in rural communities. Secretary Perdue also spoke about the role of technology in agriculture, the importance of trade, and the need for broadband connectivity in rural areas. The briefing also touched on topics such as the President's strategy with China, the special election in Georgia, climate change, and the Russian probe.